### 1. Sign Up

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/v1/signup \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
 "firstName": "john",
 "lastName": "Jis",
 "password": "pass",
 "userName": "dan",
 "email": "sss@gmail.com"
}'
```

### 2. Login

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/v1/login \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
 "username": "dan",
 "password": "pass"
}'
```

### 3. Refresh Token

Assuming you have a refresh token, replace `your-refresh-token` with the actual token:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/v1/refresh-token \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
 "refreshToken": "your-refresh-token"
}'
```

### 4. Logout

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/v1/logout
```

### Notes:

- Ensure your server is running and accessible at `localhost:8081`.
- Replace any placeholder values (like `your-refresh-token`) with actual values you have.
- If you encounter any issues, check the server logs for more detailed error messages.
